<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum9/HTML/000968.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">pfb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have to yet to find a decent non-standard (read: sword) weapon - I am currently playing as a Survivor specalising in maces - and haven't found a decent one yet (only a tailored morningstar - twice)...but swords have been abundant (and some nice ones as well)...why?  And are there any nice maces in the game?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Elliot Kane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">All of the best weapons in the game are awords, and most of them are two handed.  This is just the way it is, unfortunately...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alarys</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Off the top of my head there are a swords, daggers, staves, maces, axes, bows, spears (or were they under staves?)<P>That's a lot of different categories, and to design content for each one takes a lot of work. Then there are the other little things like the huge amount of quests, dialogue, monsters and other items to do ;-) I imagine swords got more of a focus, since the tendancy in RPG's is to use swords.<P>I guess the moral is "you can't please everyone, all the time". With unlimited time and budget I'm sure you could come close though. Too bad Larian didn't have that, or I'm sure it would have been pointless to release another RPG since it would be that good ;-)</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">pfb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NWN tried it's best with it's limited selection - and Morrowind did (imo) very well with the ability to enchant a weapon with spells...<P>Oh well, might as well stop putting points into Mace specialisation then...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">anakinda</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have found a couple great maces, they are rare though I do admit.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fargol</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I never found a decent mace. Found a few decent staffs, though they did little damage. Found one or two good spears (with Frost), and some good axes. I recall a couple nice hammers, but hammers, like axes, are slow.<P>But swords far and away are the best. Don't understand why the designers made it that way, frankly.<P>I also found a fair number of Bows with good high-end damage (~140), and with Poison Weapon they are formidable.<P>Rick</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I did find a very good axe very late in the game - I only wished I had found it earlier...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">swampdragom</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">     I can't remember ever playing a game where players complain about finding good maces and spears but no good swords. Players know that and specialize in swords and bows over other weapons. Designers know that players do that and go to more trouble to put good swords in the game. The cycle continues...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">viperboy207</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Its obvious the warrior lives or dies by melee fighting so thats why they put better swords in the game then the rest of the weapons.where as the survivor and mage both rely more on ranged attacks.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Killbomb</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I found an awesome axe not far into the wasteland. "Axe of a Hundred Crusades" I believe it was called. I finally got to switch over from the Lich's Claymore of Stunning that I'd been using forever.  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> Good thing I had all those extra points to put into axe mastery. Hehe. Good equipment is VERY rare it seems...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DE</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't think having a good variety of each kind of weapon is something that takes a lot of development effort. The weapons are almost all generated randomly and most look the same, but just have different kind of effects. It would hardly have broken the programming budget to generate the same sorts of enhancements for all of the weapons type - and in fact they do, but some reason the swords come out way more frequently, and with higher bonuses. Probably, just an oversight in the code. Since they went to all of the effort to give specialization in all of the variouse weapon types, it would be nice if actually was a useful skill.<P>I have found quite a few powerful Axes. I have one that does 70-120 damage with a few stat boasts and a really nice bow that does 40-178 damage. My best sword only does 30-70, but has frost, which more then makes up for the lower hit points.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
